{@--2@} (Gram.) 
Extended application, application by 
analogy, transference of one 
attribute to another, attraction of one
case or rule to another; {#atideSo nAma#}
{#itaraDarmasya itarasmin prayogAya AdeSaH#} ( 
{#mImAMsA#}); or {#anyatrEva praRItAyAH kftsnAyA#} 
{#DarmasaMhateH . anyatra kAryataH prAptiratideSaH sa ucyate..#}
{#prAkftAt karmaRo yasmAttatsamAnezu karmasu .#} 
{#DarmapraveSo yena syAdatideSaH sa ucyate ..#} This
{#atideSa#} is of {5} kinds: {#SAstra°, kArya°#}, 
{#nimitta°, vyapadeSa°#} & {#rUpa°#}. Thus in Grammar
{#prakftivat vikftiH, karmaRA karmavattulyakriyaH#} or
{#puMvat, Ridvat, vyapadeSIvadBAvaH & iRvadikaH#} are
instances. {#gosadfSo gavayaH#} is an instance
of {#rUpAtideSa#} or analogy;  
{#vAkyArTasyAtideSasya smftirvyApAra ucyate#}  
<ls>Bhāṣā P. 80.</ls> {#atideSa#} is generally expressed by
words showing likeness or 
resemblance, such as {#iva, vat, sadfSa#} &c.
